						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up outside the Vēṇugōpālasvāmi temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Pārthiva, Pushya ba. 10, Sunday.</p>						

						<p>Records the permission accorded by a certain Kurimēḍi Sarvānāyiniṅgāru to the tenants of Kaṁbhaṁpāḍu to set up mortar and pestle in the fields for pounding grain and cooking their food during harvest time.</p>						

